title: FBI Files related to Thomas Carlyle Rabbitt Jr. held by the National Archives and Record Administration

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

A review and release of all FBI documents related to the radical 20th century Seattle political figure Thomas Carlyle Rabbitt, Jr. 

According to the FBI all documentation related to Thomas Carlyle Rabbitt, Jr. was transferred to NARA. Here's a link to a message from the FBI that mentions relevant file numbers transferred to NARA: https://cdn.muckrock.com/foia_files/2024/12/18/E7908104761ada90102dbb251d5ef1507ebdb2b85632a2800ec_Q234447_D165372200.pdf

The following file numbers were cited as being relevant to Thomas Carlyle Rabbitt, Jr., and are now under the control of NARA:

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you for NARA's commitment to transparency. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robert Delaware
